Ah perfect, thanks for clarifying! Here's a **simple step-by-step instruction** format for the black bar removal task that you can copy into your document:

---

### 🛠 Task: Remove the Black Bar Under Table Headers

**Follow these steps exactly:**

| Step | What to Click | What to Look For |
|------|----------------|------------------|
| 1 | Go to **Dev Studio** ▶ **Records** ▶ **User Interface** ▶ **Skin** ▶ Open `SCE Enterprise` |
| 2 | In the Skin rule, go to the **Component styles** tab |
| 3 | In the left panel, expand **Layouts** ▶ **Trees and Tables** |
| 4 | Click on the **Default** format under “My Formats” |
| 5 | Click on the **Column headings** tab |
| 6 | Expand the **Border** section |
| 7 | ✅ Enable the checkbox for **Use default border for this format** |
| 8 | 📸 You’ll see the black bar under “Color | Amount | Label” is now removed in the preview on the right |
| 9 | Click **Save** at the top-right |
| 10 | 🔁 Clear the cache if needed (Ctrl + Shift + R or use "Configure ▶ System ▶ Release ▶ Clear Caches") to see changes live |

---

